with differential given by
2176hodge-theory-iii-5.1.9.2hodge-theory-iii-5.1.9.2.xmlEquation5.1.9.2hodge-theory-iii-5.1.9 \mathrm {d}(x^{pq}) = \mathrm {d}_K(x^{pq}) + (-1)^p\sum _i(-1)^i\delta _i x^{pq}. \tag{5.1.9.2}
We denote by L the second filtration of \mathrm {s}{K}, i.e.
